Q9 Comment: After the first few weeks it was clear that I would not learn anything by going to my lectures. Instead I used UW's Open Math resource and textbook to approximate a lecture during my scheduled time frame. Going to lecture was not an efficient use of my time.
Q10 Comment: This course would benefit greatly from weekly assignments as opposed to weekly quizzes. The quizzes for this course were usually out of 10 - 12 marks, which meant that not understanding / making a simple mistake on one question dropped your mark by a significant percentage. It's extremely disheartening to put in hours upon hours of work into a particular skill only to get a 60% because the quiz is out of 10 and you run out of time etc. Assignments would allow students to tackle harder problems than presented on the quiz (to get a better gauge of their understanding) while also allowing the students to spend the amount of time that is appropriate to them to finish it.
